Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.59,0:00:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain rises on a mysterious new era...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.47,0:00:05.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Monday 7:00 reasoning show.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.68,0:00:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the puzzling case of the "Fuurinkazan."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.68,0:00:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan and Heiji bring it to its final conclusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.73,0:00:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:13.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.27,0:00:15.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.26,0:01:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The feuding Torada and Tatsuo families\Nare involved in a serial murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.32,0:02:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crimes are being patterned\Nafter Takeda Shingen's "Fuurinkazan."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is the culprit so obsessed with Shingen?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.38,0:02:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's the connection with the falling\Ndeath of Officer Kai Kuroto six years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.60,0:02:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the mystery deepens, eventually there's a new victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.53,0:02:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's been burnt black from top to bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.11,0:02:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But looking at the shape, there's no doubt it was Torada Shigetsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.99,0:02:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Tatsuo family must have done this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.50,0:02:37.89,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)}Torada Naonobu (61)\N{\fs10} Head of the Torada Family
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.08,0:02:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of foolish talk is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.12,0:02:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, where\Ndid that fishing pole go?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.21,0:02:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fishing pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.25,0:02:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It was in a case, but I think it was probably a fishing pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.05,0:02:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, a fishing pole? Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.22,0:02:48.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.74,0:02:54.20,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} touched the train's aerial electrical wiring\Nwith this long fishing pole and was electrocuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.85,0:02:54.20,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)} Torada Yui (29)\N{\fs12} Yoshirou's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.64,0:02:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did you find that pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.98,0:02:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right there in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The case for the pole had been\Ndropped over by the railroad crossing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.65,0:03:06.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he must have taken it out there, and\Nafter he was hit by the electrical shock...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figure it must have been struck by the train and hurled there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.87,0:03:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And next to the case, someone has placed the corpse of a centipede.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.20,0:03:18.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is another serial murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.75,0:03:22.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Torada Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was killed by a tornado, is "wind".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.46,0:03:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was buried in the\Nground and beaten to death, is "mountain".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.67,0:03:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was hanged in the woods, is "forest".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.05,0:03:37.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Torada Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who received an electrical\Nshock and was burned completely black, is "fire".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.18,0:03:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Fuurinkazan" has been successfully completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.15,0:03:44.90,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Akira (32)\N{\fs13} Tamefumi's Son
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.39,0:03:46.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But, why did my wife and my friends\Nhave to be killed in this horrible way?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.53,0:03:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yamato, there's\Na strange notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.24,0:03:50.16,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,0)}Yamato Kansuke (35)\N{\fs12} Nagano Prefectural\NPolice Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.70,0:03:52.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This seems to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.16,0:03:56.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A record of their progress in searching for the buried gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.70,0:04:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, could that possibly be the memo pad\Nthat Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.42,0:04:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but this was also used as a shared diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.42,0:04:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In summary, what's written in the diary says...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.01,0:04:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That six years ago they accidentally caused a certain person's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:18.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They fought with the idea of going to the police\Nor not, but in the end, they didn't say anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.64,0:04:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they've remained silent ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.81,0:04:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Akira, they did it for your sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:30.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second. Six years ago? That means the dead person was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.49,0:04:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.78,0:04:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Kai Kuroto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.87,0:04:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that you would win at the preliminary contest\Nand be chosen as the horseback archery bowman...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.41,0:04:42.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wanted to cause Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to be injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.37,0:04:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They used fireworks to frighten Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s horse\Nwhile he was practicing, hoping he'd be thrown.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.21,0:04:51.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the horse became more frightened\Nthat they thought, and it started running.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.55,0:04:52.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when they followed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.97,0:04:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says they found that Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, along\Nwith his horse, had fallen off the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.72,0:04:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.35,0:05:03.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the handwriting, I'd say four\Npeople were writing in this shared diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.06,0:05:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd dare say it's those who've recently died:\NYoshirou and Shigetsugu from the Torada family...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.32,0:05:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Kouji and Ayaka from the Tatsuo family, those four people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.24,0:05:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would that notebook be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.70,0:05:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to send it to hell, and keep all of this hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.24,0:05:22.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu made a show of looking for this note-\Nbook, but in truth he had it concealed on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.04,0:05:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He kept hold of it as he burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.08,0:05:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that was his way of apologizing to Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.00,0:05:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're not saying, this series of murders was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.38,0:05:32.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After consigning his partners in the crime six years ago to oblivion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.09,0:05:38.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As his last act, he killed himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.43,0:05:41.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to bury the truth in darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Torada Shigetsugu was the serial murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.35,0:05:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason he attempted to destroy this notebook...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.40,0:05:50.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was so Tatsuo Akira would never know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.11,0:05:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, unfortunately for him, since it got hurled\Naway without being burned, it remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.05,0:05:57.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Still, if it was done in some part for Akira's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.00,0:06:01.55,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that, in the other world, he'll acknowledge him for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:06:01.55,CharCard05,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)} Tatsuo Tamefumi (56)\N{\fs11} Head of the Tatsuo Family
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:06:01.55,CharCard06,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)} Tatsuo Shigeyo (78)\N{\fs11} Tamefumi's Mother
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.04,0:06:05.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, this case is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.46,0:06:12.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this situation, I'd like to tell you all to\Nreturn peacefully to your homes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.21,0:06:16.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To complete my checking on this case, I need to\Nsearch your houses, so wait here for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.64,0:06:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, did Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} actually find that notebook?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.68,0:06:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I didn't see him find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.81,0:06:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stopped searching and\Nstarted reading his cellphone e-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.78,0:06:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So maybe he did find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.82,0:06:35.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.03,0:06:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, I saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.32,0:06:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just when we were about to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.62,0:06:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.83,0:06:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji-niichan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.58,0:06:47.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it? Did you find something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.25,0:06:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.71,0:06:54.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A rock with a string attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.05,0:06:59.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, there was a string attached to that notebook too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.47,0:07:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bah, what does it matter? The case is already over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.93,0:07:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} burned, that was "fire", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.68,0:07:07.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.69,0:07:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lightning? Does that mean it's going to rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.40,0:07:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lightning?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.82,0:07:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it "lightning?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.19,0:07:26.30,CharCard07,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)} Torada Tatsue (58)\N{\fs13} Naonobu's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.89,0:07:23.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This is annoying, to think we're being made\Nto wait here in the middle of the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.23,0:07:27.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, it was raining on the day my\Nhusband and the others killed Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.71,0:07:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband started having a lot of nightmares.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.08,0:07:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would mutter, "The sound... the flash..."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He meant the lightning, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.84,0:07:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it was sunny that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.47,0:07:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.76,0:07:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My poor Shigetsugu will get rained on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Heiji, can't you do something about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.27,0:07:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.64,0:07:49.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.94,0:07:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those guys went off on their own again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.02,0:07:55.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here below the place where Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hanged...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.82,0:07:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are no one else's footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.94,0:07:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.36,0:08:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are just the footprints and the marks of his cane that\Ndetective Yamato made when he brought the body down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.74,0:08:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When could the culprit have hanged Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.25,0:08:12.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} disappeared from the restroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.67,0:08:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both us and the members of the Torada family were there together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.09,0:08:21.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the people from the Tatsuo family were\Nbeing driven over by Tamefumi in his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.59,0:08:22.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.43,0:08:25.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.85,0:08:27.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's the police detective we met earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.93,0:08:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.31,0:08:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it looks like it's going to rain, Inspector\NYamato told us to come cover the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.06,0:08:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Whose coat is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.07,0:08:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found this earlier, caught in a tree branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.19,0:08:41.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, that coat...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.74,0:08:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it wet?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.70,0:08:45.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. The inspector asked me the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.78,0:08:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's not wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.12,0:08:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, please keep out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.46,0:08:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since the inspector came back, he's kept us\Nworking hard without even letting us have a day off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:08:58.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Came back"? Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.42,0:09:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We went up into the mountains to find a man who had\Nskipped on his parole and got caught in an avalanche.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.59,0:09:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man was someone Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had arrested for stealing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.35,0:09:11.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he'd vanished six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.39,0:09:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yamato thought he might be\Nconnected to Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s accidental death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.69,0:09:19.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to that, the inspector's left eye and left leg were injured...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.40,0:09:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he was unconscious the whole time that he was in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.15,0:09:26.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And did that man have any connection to Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.74,0:09:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it turned out they were unrelated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.20,0:09:32.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But fate sure is cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.87,0:09:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who was his junior officer before he left, Uehara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next time they met, she was the wife of a victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.17,0:09:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though Uehara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said they had to be absolutely\Nsure about what really happened when Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.93,0:09:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And despite both she and the inspector being so enthusiastic about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.80,0:09:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She suddenly quit her job as a detective and got married.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.68,0:09:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard that those two became police detectives\Nin the first place because they admired Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.14,0:09:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's so, then when she found Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nbody six years ago, she was a police detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.44,0:10:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, since she was still new, it was a terrible\Nexperience for her and she cried over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.53,0:10:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of crying, there's one thing that's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.70,0:10:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.49,0:10:14.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsuo Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Even though she must have\Nwiped away some tears before she died...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.71,0:10:16.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no other trace of her having cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.87,0:10:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know she wiped tears away?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.79,0:10:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The eye shadow in her left eye had been rubbed,\Nand some of it was still on her right index finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.72,0:10:26.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that make you think she wiped tears away?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What color was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:30.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What color?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.14,0:10:31.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.85,0:10:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just common blue eye shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:39.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, lead your dark bay back to the Torada house right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.66,0:10:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.12,0:10:43.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.07,0:10:47.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears that this war...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.02,0:11:02.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Torada House
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.10,0:11:02.84,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What? The police are coming to search the house again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.30,0:11:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Inspector Yamato along with some of his junior officers will\Nbe coming tomorrow and staying over while they investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.51,0:11:11.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, they'll be searching the Tatsuo\Nhouse in the same way starting tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.80,0:11:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long will they be staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.76,0:11:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will be three or four days, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.98,0:11:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three or four days?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.27,0:11:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember right, the festival is three days from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.52,0:11:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll have started.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.44,0:11:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.86,0:11:27.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The festival, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.32,0:11:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\b1}Tatsuo House
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.99,0:11:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.99,0:11:34.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kouji.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.56,0:11:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.61,0:11:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.41,0:11:41.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you do that to Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r} just to help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.00,0:11:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.22,0:11:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was you, just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.76,0:11:54.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Torada Yui{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.76,0:11:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? So you knew?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.31,0:11:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I'd be coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.64,0:11:59.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.64,0:12:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because of what you said to yourself\Nwhen Shigetsugu died: "lightning."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.52,0:12:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While it's true that Shigetsugu san's body was\Nburned, the cause of his death was electrocution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.11,0:12:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That wasn't "fire", it was the "lightning"\Nfrom "Move like the lightning."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.24,0:12:19.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. There's more to the "Fuurinkazan"\Nstrategy that Sun Tzu advocated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.29,0:12:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Move like the lightning" that you just mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.79,0:12:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as impenetrable as a shadow."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.21,0:12:33.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "lightning" comes from "When you appear,\Nappear unexpectedly like the lightning."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.47,0:12:37.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shadow" is from "When you hide, hide as still as a shadow."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.89,0:12:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.18,0:12:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the same way with Kai san, beneath the cliff where the\Nsun didn't reach throughout the day, his breath growing still.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.15,0:12:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To those four who caused Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death six years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.69,0:12:52.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His blood soaked undershirt must have looked deep red.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.99,0:12:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like the calvary troops wore in Takeda's "Akazonae".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.33,0:13:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why this was all patterned after Shingen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.12,0:13:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was to flush out those four who caused Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.92,0:13:09.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as expected, Kouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} reacted to it almost instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.00,0:13:13.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} weren't that interested in Shingen...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.72,0:13:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they didn't respond to the corpses of the centipedes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.89,0:13:20.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, it was with all that uproar that\Noccurred over the Suwa-style helmet...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.10,0:13:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was finally smoked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.35,0:13:25.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then Ayaka was forced to revealed Shigetsugu's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.06,0:13:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you come to deal with me just like you did those four!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.28,0:13:32.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To wipe out Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r}'s rival!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.74,0:13:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deal with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.24,0:13:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.16,0:13:39.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came here to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.87,0:13:42.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the person who's behind these serial murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.50,0:13:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From that person there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.84,0:13:48.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.21,0:13:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should have expected it from a former policewoman.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.84,0:13:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you figure it out, I wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.01,0:13:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the blue eye shadow on Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.43,0:14:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ao" (blue) from "aokage" (dark bay), meaning a black horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.72,0:14:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.10,0:14:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person riding a black horse at the time, which was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.19,0:14:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a clever little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.23,0:14:13.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you forced Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s name\Nout of Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and dealt with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.24,0:14:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the child of my husband's former wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.20,0:14:20.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wasn't related to me by blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.78,0:14:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why, Tatsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.25,0:14:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because she's the one who really killed Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.58,0:14:32.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mentioned it earlier, that my husband would say, "The\Nsound, the flash..." while he was having nightmares.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.46,0:14:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what lead me to realize there was another\Nperson at the crime scene six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.97,0:14:39.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it was you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:43.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I wanted him injured as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.56,0:14:47.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I fired one shot from this gun at his horse's legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.10,0:14:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when he plunged head over heels off the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.15,0:14:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, wouldn't you know, some people\Ncame and started making a big fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.69,0:14:58.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if they were the ones who caused his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.28,0:14:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That just made me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.24,0:15:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would have been best if they continued\Nto think that and kept quiet, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.29,0:15:08.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later on, he started talking about going to tell the police\Nabout the gunshot he'd heard and the flash he'd seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.00,0:15:13.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then the gods punished Yoshirou by sending him that tornado.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.92,0:15:17.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you left my severely injured husband there to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.38,0:15:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leaving the centipede corpse you had already prepared there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.09,0:15:26.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, by that time, I'd already hit upon the idea of\Npatterning everything after the "Fuu-rin-ka-zan-in-rai".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.64,0:15:32.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that means one of your targets right from the start was Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.36,0:15:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the final one—\h"fire."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.53,0:15:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you've become a hindrance to the gambling\Nthat we sponsor, you'll be burned to a crisp.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.45,0:15:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll cook you with these flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.04,0:15:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gambling?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.54,0:15:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They gamble on the festival horseback archery demonstration,\Nbetting how many of the ten shots will be missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.63,0:15:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never missed a single one...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.96,0:15:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until you shifted one of the targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.13,0:16:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no point in gambling if he never misses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.26,0:16:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since you've hit them all for five years\Nstraight as well, you'll need to die too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.18,0:16:08.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The story will be that you took revenge for\Nyour Kai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r}, whom you loved dearly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.73,0:16:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then to atone for those crimes, you took your own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.11,0:16:15.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But considering the current circumstances...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.98,0:16:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having this stupid woman who, to solve the mystery of Officer Kai's\Ndeath, went so far as to marry Yoshirou, a man she didn't love...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.16,0:16:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It might look better if we change our story to\None where she kills you out of resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.16,0:16:31.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, will you tell this stupid woman something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.54,0:16:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why were there no marks beneath the place\Nwhere Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hanged on the tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.13,0:16:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why waste words on someone about to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.01,0:16:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.72,0:16:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Back then, you put Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on your horse, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.68,0:16:51.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used a rope you had already attached to the branch beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.06,0:16:53.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allowing you to hook it to her neck from the other side of the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.56,0:16:58.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, you rode your horse up behind the tree...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.07,0:17:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So no one would know when the hoof marks had gotten there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.32,0:17:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long have you been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.24,0:17:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as swift as the wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.83,0:17:10.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting here for two hours before you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.54,0:17:15.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, the reason no one noticed\Nthat Ayaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was on your horse was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.84,0:17:19.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had put a black coat on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.76,0:17:24.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Ayaka san was secluded in the restroom, you called\Nher by cellphone and secretly lured her out to the stables.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.59,0:17:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Akira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others left on the horses...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.30,0:17:31.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You placed her, with that black coat on her,\Nonto your black horse and went into the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.81,0:17:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.35,0:17:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You too!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.73,0:17:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as quiet as the forest."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.77,0:17:39.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting here, holding my breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.07,0:17:42.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it looks like an earlier visitor got here before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.99,0:17:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An earlier visitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.45,0:17:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you know your target...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.83,0:17:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be cool and level...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.58,0:17:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sit yourself down and observe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.58,0:18:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be immovable like the mountain."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.97,0:18:06.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You planned this, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.59,0:18:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, with the police sticking around here until\Nthe festival, tonight was your only chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.56,0:18:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, compared to your plan of swiping that note-\Nbook, hanging it from the electric train wires...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.19,0:18:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And thereby electrocuting Shigetsugu, my plan was no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.99,0:18:26.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way you used a string to tie the notebook to a rock...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.20,0:18:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Made it simple to throw up and catch it on the aerial train wires.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.83,0:18:33.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigetsugu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} learned where it was from an e-mail you sent...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.25,0:18:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when he used the pole to get it, he was electrocuted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.42,0:18:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, if you want to start a fire, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.63,0:18:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already called the fire department\Nand have them waiting on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.88,0:18:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get them!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.64,0:18:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'm striking with the blunt side.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.07,0:19:06.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.41,0:19:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.20,0:19:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eat this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.08,0:19:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saved the best for yourself again, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.67,0:19:24.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An thus, the final murder was prevented before it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.63,0:19:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the war that had lasted for six years...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.30,0:19:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was over at last, with the enemy\Ngeneral sporting a bruise on her left eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.26,0:19:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You fought a battle with the culprit and her gang last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.94,0:19:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you invite us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.06,0:19:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after all the support we've given you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.36,0:19:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiots, how could I get you involved in such a dangerous situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.49,0:19:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, please come in for a formal interview later.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.07,0:19:53.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.16,0:19:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You need to come to the police as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.04,0:19:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.34,0:20:07.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as swift as the wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.65,0:20:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.85,0:20:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because I thought you were dead, Kan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.89,0:20:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I thought I had to do something...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.44,0:20:25.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I married Yoshirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.90,0:20:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, when I say it like that, it makes me feel sorry for my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.36,0:20:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, didn't I just say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.70,0:20:34.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Come to the police."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.91,0:20:40.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you free yourself from your obligations,\Nand when you're ready —\hcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.21,0:20:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chief detective has been waiting too —\Nto taste that awful coffee you make again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.80,0:20:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, somehow those two...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.18,0:20:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are getting along!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.02,0:21:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, what did those two say?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.02,0:21:03.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were standing next to them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.73,0:21:06.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said, "Be as swift as the wind" or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.90,0:21:10.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The strategy of love!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.15,0:21:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fuurinkazan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.19,0:22:34.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.86,0:22:36.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Kazuha?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.74,0:22:37.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, just c'mon!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.20,0:22:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.87,0:22:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's from Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.33,0:22:47.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, hello, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.92,0:22:50.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ran. What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.92,0:22:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.59,0:22:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today! Today's when I'm going to tell you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.72,0:22:56.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't we talk later?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.97,0:22:59.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! It's no good if we don't talk now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.64,0:23:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as swift as the wind."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.85,0:23:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry. I gotta go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.27,0:23:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! Don't try and run away, Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.81,0:23:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Attack as fiercely as the fire."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.90,0:23:20.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be as quiet as the forest."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.53,0:23:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. It might be better to talk later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.79,0:23:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, why don't we leave it there for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.46,0:23:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.26,0:23:37.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.76,0:23:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.09,0:23:41.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think they're getting irritable because they're hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.64,0:23:47.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be immovable like the mountain."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.90,0:24:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.70,0:24:24.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,FOX\N(kitsune)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.05,0:24:26.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The setting next time is Yamaguchi Prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.48,0:24:27.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Will I be going to?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.16,0:24:27.95,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,You're not needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.97,0:24:29.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The broadcast is on Dec 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.98,0:24:30.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the next episode
